parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and shutting off of the engine can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the instrument panel displays warning messages
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption and leaks can lead to engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause a fire, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: the vehicle requires frequent oil changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, which can lead to engine damage, stalling, and potentially cause a fire, compromising vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: the instrument panel displays warning messages

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and massive failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of critical safety features, such as headlights, interior lights, and door locks, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in bad weather conditions.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power to various accessories
and rear AC blower. Intermittent failure of interior lights and headlights
resulting in dim or no lighting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of critical safety features, such as headlights and interior lights, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in bad weather conditions.
symptoms: resulting in delayed or no lighting after starting the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Panel and Mirror Adjustment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loose covers for the window and mirror adjustment buttons can cause a safety hazard, especially at night, when trying to adjust the mirrors.
symptoms: Loose covers for the window and mirror adjustment buttons
requiring replacement of the entire door panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of interior lights and dim headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Interior lights flicker or work intermittently
headlights are dim or have reduced brightness
lights may not turn on or off as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dim or failed headlights can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights are dim or have reduced brightness
reduced visibility while driving at night or in low-light conditions.
